@{b}Train Driver 3@{ub}



Modular Train Driver Simulator

Following on from Train Driver 2, this new version
has many new features, to allow loading of any route with
more details.


    Requirements:

    @{b}Any Amiga with at least 2 mb (including 1 mb chip mem) and WB2.04+@{ub}

    Recommended:

    Hard Drive
    A1200 or better


There are three ways of using Train Driver 3

 * Generate a random route by adjusting the sliders on the Loading Screen
   The random routes generated by TD3 will be different from those generated by TD2 with the same code

 * Load data from a real railway route

 * Create a real or fictional route using Data files or
   Train Driver Route Editor


TD Features:



 Semaphore signals; 2, 3 or 4 aspect colour light signals; RETB signals
 Guard, station and signalman speech
 Scenery including buildings and trees
 Up to 4 locos on each train
 Double tracks for loops, platforms, Slow/Goods Lines.
 Signal route indicators
 Random loco failures
 Weather seasons
 Variable fog visibility
 Reasons for delays displayed
 Tool Types preferences for Driver, Vigilance, Speech, Clock speed, Confirm Quit, Low memory, Intro On/Off, Detail level

   And new for TD3....

 Up to 100% Quicker Frame Rate
 Trains visible on the other track - 11 different classes
 Full Steam loco controls - regulator, cutoff valve, water injectors, blowers, fire door, coal shovelling etc.
 Points visible
 Option to Save or Print Log file
 Adjust buildings base height and position (X and Y co-ords)
 Variable line names
 Junction signal probability adjustable
 Define station stops arrival times
 Electric wires on/off during route with telegraph poles alternative
 New sounds at stations - guard, whistle, bells
 Holding brakes on gradients
 Better gradient response
 Guard stops train if station stop missed or "R" ignored
 Option to run Driver Only
 Advance warning of junction speeds and line speed reductions
 Visible steam and improved steam sound effects
 Horizon buildings
 Electric Token Block signalling system (RETB)
 Tunnels can now be any distance apart (ie less than half a mile)
 Driver's career log and points system
 Hi detail option with sleepers

  And new in the latest version for registered users...

 Third Rail DC electric locos and routes supported
 Signals can now be restricted to certain aspects
 Station platform lengths variable for main stations
 Improved scenery rendering
 Change locos at stations en-route
 New T indicator to indicate when rear of train is on a lower speed limit section
 New opportunities to gain and lose points!
 Change train load and length at main stations
 Internal timings on loaded routes now allow extra time for uphill gradients
 Press s on timings screen to save to file
 Up to 7 lines now visible with signals
 Trains now visibly cross to other lines at junctions
 New improved chart screen allows review of your driving
 Joystick control option
 Platforms adjust to nearest rail
 Option to terminate short of end of line
 TD3 now supports units (trains with engines mounted under the coaches) eg 150 Sprinters, 321 EMUs
 Preceding slow trains
 Request, Set Down Only, Pick Up only stops added


